      "message": "Having a pool of surfaces has two features. Not sure if they\u0027re critical, so I can try your suggestion and time:\n\n- If we get ahead of the encoder (i.e. more rendered images exist than workers) snapping involves at least a malloc, (hopefully not a copy if our erase optimization kicks in). With a pool of surfaces, there are no mallocs/free between frames.\n- The fixed pool throttles our memory usage, in case we get way ahead of the encoder (or just a slow frame).",
